1 unit Lemon
2 unit Scallions
1 unit Mini Cucumber
2 tablespoon Mayonnaise
1 unit Apricot Jam
1 teaspoon Sriracha
4 ounce Coleslaw Mix
2 unit Flour Tortillas
5 ounce Spinach
1 tablespoon Olive Oil
Salt
Pepper

• Wash and dry produce.

• Trim cucumber and halve lengthwise; cut into thin wedges. Quarter lemon.
Thinly slice scallions.

• In a small bowl, toss cucumber with juice from one lemon wedge
(two lemon wedges for 4 servings), salt, and pepper.

• In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, jam, Sriracha, 1 TBSP olive oil, and
juice from one lemon wedge (for 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil and juice
from two lemon wedges). Season with salt and pepper.

• To bowl with dressing, add spinach, coleslaw mix, and scallions; toss to coat.

• Wrap tortillas in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and pliable,
90 seconds.

• Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Place cucumber on the bottom two-thirds of each tortilla and top with as much spinach salad as you like. Fold
up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides
toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

• Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates and serve with any
remaining spinach salad on the side.